KW  - First-price auctions
KW  - Models of entry
KW  - Selective entry
KW  - Selection effect
KW  - Nonparametric estimation
KW  - Quantiles
AB  - We develop a selective entry model for first-price auctions that nests two polar models often estimated in the empirical literature on auctions, Levin and Smith (1994), and Samuelson (1985). The selective entry model features a pro-competitive selection effect. The selection effect is shown to be nonparametrically identifiable, and a nonparametric test for its presence is proposed. This test can be used to discriminate between the two polar models.
